President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key leadership positions in his administration. Melissa G. Dalton is nominated to be Under Secretary of the Air Force in the Department of Defense. She currently serves as the Assistant Secretary of Defense for Homeland Defense and Hemispheric Affairs, where she advises senior defense leaders on defense continuity and mission assurance, homeland defense, and defense support of civil authorities. Andrew Plitt is nominated to be Assistant Administrator for the Middle East at the U.S. Agency for International Development. He currently serves as USAID's Senior Deputy Assistant Administrator for the Middle East region, overseeing policy, strategy, resources, and operations in the Middle East and North Africa. Tanya F. Otsuka is nominated to be a Member of the Board of Directors of the National Credit Union Administration Board. She currently works as Senior Counsel for the majority staff of the U.S. Senate Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs Committee, where she handles banking and credit union issues. Spencer Bachus III is nominated to be a Member (Republican) of the Board of Directors of the Export-Import Bank of the United States. He has been a member of the EXIM Board of Directors since 2019 and previously served as a member of the House of Representatives from Alabama. Bachus has worked on committees related to transportation and infrastructure, judiciary, and financial services during his time in Congress.